==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Physics
<hw>Phys"ics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Physic</er>.]</ety> <def>The science of nature, or of natural
objects; that branch of science which treats of the laws and properties
of matter, and the forces acting upon it; especially, that department of
natural science which treats of the causes (as gravitation, heat, light,
magnetism, electricity, etc.) that modify the general properties of
bodies; natural philosophy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Chemistry</xex>, though a branch of <xex>general
physics</xex>, is commonly treated as a science by itself, and the
application of physical principles which it involves constitute a branch
called <xex>chemical physics</xex>, which treats more especially of
those physical properties of matter which are used by chemists in
defining and distinguishing substances.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Physiocrat</ent>⟦br⟧
